article.description: James Madison's late drive beats Lehigh 31-28
article.headline: James Madison's late drive beats Lehigh 31-28
article.linkText: James Madison's late drive beats Lehigh 31-28
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. -- James Madison mounted two last-ditch efforts -- a 98-yard scoring drive and then blocked a chip-shot field goal -- to rally past Lehigh 31-28 on Saturday. Jauan Latney scored from the 6 to cap the 98-yard grinder of a drive late in the game. Freshman John Miller rushed for 60 of his 106 yards on the final drive and also scored on a 9-yard run after halftime. The Dukes (1-1) trailed 21-10 after a half, but turned it around after a 38-minute lightning delay to start the third quarter. Lehigh (0-1) mounted one last drive in the final 4 minutes, advancing to the 10 to line up for a fourth-down field goal with 51 seconds left. James Madison frosh Jimmy Moreland came around the left side and blocked the 27-yard potential game-tier. Lehigh's Nick Shafnisky passed for 214 yards and two TDs, and also ran for 121 yards.
